  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.3-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 18.04\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen using puppeth to deploy a wallet service, it should run properly\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nwallet service container is simply crashing & rebooting\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n- Install Geth 1.10.3-stable\r\n- With puppeth deploy  ethstats, bootnode & sealnode => those stetps are working fine\r\n- try to deploy wallet and it is not working\r\n\r\nFailing docker image :\r\n```\r\npuppeth/wallet       latest    fc77afa3c3eb   2 years ago         443MB\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nUsing docker logs on wallet image\r\n\r\n````\r\nGeth\r\nVERSION:\r\n   1.9.0-unstable-43e1b7b1\r\n...\r\nIncorrect Usage. flag provided but not defined: -http\r\n\r\n````\r\nOn the Wallet Dockerfile :\r\nThis is the failling command that uses the -http\r\necho $'exec geth --networkid 4242 --port 30304 --bootnodes enode://55b888e5e5f0c4fcd41b5c7d86bcb8c6eb5c03ef8134c6fced3b2cff6f78da86a5b69d7d657e8550227f51fa505fac2c215adc0255b9090937126ba74b4d3453@10.60.42.2:30303 --ethstats \\'wallet:testchain@10.60.42.2:8081\\' --cache=512 --http --http.addr=0.0.0.0 --http.corsdomain \"*\" --http.vhosts \"*\"' >> wallet.sh\r\n\r\nWhen submitting logs: please submit them as text and not screenshots.",
